#Ground Plane Fitting
repo
@inproceedings{Zermas2017Fast, title={Fast segmentation of 3D point clouds: A paradigm on LiDAR data for autonomous vehicle applications}, author={Zermas, Dimitris and Izzat, Izzat and Papanikolopoulos, Nikolaos}, booktitle={IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation}, year={2017}, }  In this paper, Zermas proposed a scan_line_based point cloud segmentation method. The ground plane is removed according to Ground Plan Fitting. Here, the ground plane model as $a*x+b*y+c*z + d = 0$. And the normal of plane is regared as the least primary component of the covariance matrix.
